{
  "stem": "11964.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "She brought me some more food, and she said that Henryk will definitely come for me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And after a few days, he did come for me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "He came with a broken-down pickup truck.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "He says he couldn't trust himself to take me to Warsaw by, by train because they had strict control, and I still didn't have any papers.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we had a very, very eventful trip, avoiding all the guards and all the-- all the road blocks and all that.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was really a very good introduction to living on Aryan papers and hiding from place to place.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he brought me to an apartment, and he introduced me to a lady in the apartment, and she was his wife.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So that was a revelation.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And right then and there he said, we got papers for your sister, and your sister is safe in a safe house, in an underground safe house, a hiding house that the underground maintains.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we have to give you false papers, but they are going to be fake papers because we couldn't get any realistically auth-- authentic papers.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he gave papers to my younger sister, and we called her Theresa Wrobelewska, and for me, Sophia, or Zosia, Wrobelewska.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And these are our first false papers because we needed false papers should there be a raid on the safe house so we had something to identify ourselves with.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were taken to that safe house.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "While we came there, we were there, there was already one couple there, a married couple there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we came, and the man who was in charge of the apartment-- it was his apartment.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
